<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,320]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from Latin 
<emphasis box="[801,872,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">niveus</emphasis>
(snowy, of snow, snow-white) in reference to the irregularly scattered grey-white scales on forewing apex (like melting snowflakes on grey background). It should be also mentioned, that this amazing new species occurs close to the Andean snowline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
